      <item>
        <title>Decoding a packet using tshark</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Sometime you want to have tshark to decode the packet (e.g. to test and compare results or if a layer is not supported in scapy). There is a command &lt;code&gt;tdecode&lt;/code&gt; to do this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Usage is very simple: &lt;code&gt;tdecode(pkt)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
